According to Section 54 of the Labour Act 2004, a pregnant employee is entitled to:

1. Leave work before confinement if medically certified (Section 54(1)(a));
2. Not work during the six weeks following her confinement (Section 54(1)(b));
3. Receive at least 50% pay for six months prior to her absence (Section 54(1)(c));
4. Be paid not less than 50% of her wages if she is absent from work due to pregnancy or confinement (Section 54(1)(c));
5. Have half an hour twice a day during her working hours for nursing her child (Section 54(1)(d)).

These entitlements apply to industrial, commercial, or agricultural undertakings.

